    <note>Kong(2) Pingzhong [901] He and his brothers, Wuzhong [3438] and Wenzhong [3439], were all registered members of the Yuanyou coalition. Kong(2) Yanzhi's [902] son. Pingzhong and Wuzhong were the fathers-in-law of Zeng(1) Ji's [1692] father, Zhun [3901]. Xiao(1) Qi [3362], the father-in-law of Wenzhong is presumed to be Xiao(1) Gu's [718] nephew on the basis of generational name and address. Wenzhong was Superintendent of mines and mints for an undated term during Shenzong's reign. Jiangxi TZ, 21.20a; Jiangxi TZ, 9.31b; XCB, 298.10a, 409.22b, 429.13a; Su Song, WJ, 59.1a. CBD, 1, 390.</note>
